# Short solution needed: "How to control volume in CLI" (ubuntu)

install alsa and launch it
$ sudo apt-get install alsa-utils
$ alsamixer

then use
$ amixer scontrols
$ amixer -c [card-number] set [control] [value]

for example:
following command will set the volume on the Master control/property of the first sound card to 100%
$ amixer -c 0 set Master 100%
